The paper deals with computing a depth function for multivariate data analysis, which involves computational geometry and algorithms (cs.CG). The time complexity of the algorithm is a significant factor, indicating that it could also belong to the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also investigates some geometric properties of the depth function, which could place it in the sub-category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the experimental results and comparisons with other depth functions suggest that it could also belong to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
